<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Raj Mahida Portfolio</title>

    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            background-color: #f4f4f4;
            color: #333;
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
        }

        header {
            background: #003366;
            color: white;
            padding: 25px;
            text-align: center;
        }

        nav {
            background: #0055a5;
            text-align: center;
            padding: 12px;
        }

        nav a {
            color: white;
            text-decoration: none;
            margin: 0 15px;
            font-weight: bold;
        }

        section {
            background: white;
            max-width: 900px;
            margin: 30px auto;
            padding: 25px;
            border-radius: 10px;
            box-shadow: 0px 2px 8px rgba(0,0,0,0.15);
        }

        h2 {
            color: #003366;
        }

        ul {
            padding-left: 20px;
        }

        .project {
            background: #f8f8f8;
            padding: 15px;
            border-left: 5px solid #0055a5;
            margin-top: 15px;
        }
    </style>
</head>

<body>

<header>
    <h1>Raj Mahida</h1>
    <p>Professional Portfolio</p>
</header>

<nav>
    <a href="#home">Home</a>
    <a href="#about">About</a>
    <a href="#experience">Experience</a>
    <a href="#skills">Skills</a>
    <a href="#projects">Projects</a>
    <a href="#education">Education</a>
</nav>

<section id="home">
    <h2>Home</h2>
    <p>
        Hi! Welcome to my portfolio. I made this so I can share my information with people who need it.
    </p>
</section>

<section id="about">
    <h2>About Me</h2>

    <p>
        Hi, my name is Raj Mahida. I am from India. I studied there and went to college there.
        Through my dedication and education, I became a Computer Engineer at IQVIA,
        where I work as the Director of Data Architectures.
        I work from home most of the time and occasionally go into the office.
        I have two wonderful kids.
        I have traveled frequently between India and America for work, family, and vacations.
    </p>
</section>

<section id="experience">
    <h2>Experience</h2>

    <p>
        I have had many experiences throughout my life, from moving from India to America,
        finding a job, and eventually becoming a Director.
    </p>

    <ul>
        <li>Moving from India to America</li>
        <li>Finding my first job</li>
        <li>Becoming a Director of Data Architectures</li>
        <li>Dealing with rude people at airports</li>
        <li>Experiencing delayed and canceled flights</li>
        <li>Overcoming disappointments and challenges at work</li>
        <li>Working through poor grades in college</li>
        <li>Working many late nights</li>
        <li>Raising two children while balancing work and family</li>
    </ul>
</section>

<section id="skills">
    <h2>Skills</h2>

    <ul>
        <li>Leadership</li>
        <li>Computer Engineering</li>
        <li>Data Architecture</li>
        <li>Problem Solving</li>
        <li>Project Management</li>
        <li>Communication</li>
        <li>Team Leadership</li>
        <li>Technology</li>
    </ul>
</section>

<section id="projects">
    <h2>Projects</h2>

    <div class="project">
        <h3>Professional Projects</h3>

        <p>
            Throughout my career I have worked on technology projects,
            helped solve computer problems,
            created presentations and slideshows for work,
            and supported many business initiatives.
        </p>
    </div>

    <div class="project">
        <h3>Family Projects</h3>

        <p>
            I helped my children create their portfolios and enjoy supporting them
            with technology and learning new skills.
        </p>
    </div>

</section>

<section id="education">
    <h2>Education</h2>

    <p>
        I studied at Doctor Babasaheb Ambedkar Marathwada University in India
        and later attended the University of Bridgeport in the United States.

        I earned my bachelor's degree in India from 2000–2005
        and continued my education in America from January 2006 through December 2007.
    </p>
</section>

</body>
</html>
